## Detailed Findings by Category

Below, we delve into each category of broker requests, providing more context, examples from communications, and how InnovAge addressed them. This illustrates not only individual resolutions but also the patterns and best practices that have formed in response.

### 1. Portal Access & Login Issues

**Nature of issues:** The **majority of incoming broker queries** revolved around accessing the InnovAge broker portal. These included brokers unable to log in, accounts not yet activated or seemingly locked, forgotten credentials, and technical login errors. Given that the broker portal is the primary tool for FMOs to contract agents and manage leads, any access problem is urgent. Specifically, we saw instances of an FMO reporting that their **portal link wasn‚Äôt working**[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem), another broker finding themselves **locked out** even after their account activation[[2]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzZtAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem), and an independent broker experiencing a **blank white screen** after login (a front-end glitch)[[3]](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:5bc83d83a48a42ee8b3177c9bb4b7f2f@thread.v2/1760033312713?context=%7B%22contextType%22:%22chat%22%7D). Sheri also noted that many routine calls are simply about **password resets or forgotten usernames**[[2]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzZtAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem) ‚Äì indicating that basic credential issues are extremely common.

**How they were addressed:** These portal issues were typically handled _immediately_ by the Broker Relations team:

- **Direct troubleshooting with the broker:** For example, when Garity‚Äôs contracting director reported the portal link down, Sheri Hernandez personally tested the links and found them operational[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). She then had Mark Cetola and Steven Mezidor reach out to the broker directly to walk through the login, ensuring any user error or local issue could be identified[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). (In the end, the broker replied ‚ÄúWorks now lol ‚Äì idk what was happening,‚Äù implying it was resolved after those checks[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem).) In Kimberly‚Äôs case (locked out account), Sheri quickly responded and **requested a phone call** with the broker to reset her access and get her into the portal[[2]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzZtAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). This one-on-one approach over the phone is effective for resolving login problems (whether by guiding a password reset or manually resetting the account on the backend).
- **Password resets and account unlocks:** If a broker simply forgot their password, the support team either walks them through the self-service reset process or triggers a password reset email. Because these requests are so frequent, the team likely has a standard operating procedure for them. Sheri‚Äôs mention that many calls are of this nature suggests that **credential issues are resolved on first contact** nearly every time, either by providing the username, verifying identity and resetting the password, or reminding the broker of the correct login steps[[2]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzZtAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem).
- **Involving IT for systemic issues:** When a technical configuration was at fault ‚Äì e.g., the **portal not loading if ‚Äú[www.‚Äù](http://www.xn--ivg/) wasn‚Äôt in the URL** ‚Äì the team took it up with IT. Anthony Horner agreed to ‚Äúcircle back to IT‚Äù to make sure the portal site loads regardless of URL format[[4]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaBAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). That fix would prevent similar login failures for all brokers. For the broker seeing a blank screen post-login (Donald‚Äôs case), Ron Zighelboim intervened immediately by contacting the broker and also discovered an issue with the **broker support hotline** putting people on hold[[3]](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:5bc83d83a48a42ee8b3177c9bb4b7f2f@thread.v2/1760033312713?context=%7B%22contextType%22:%22chat%22%7D). He indicated he had already reported that phone line problem earlier (so the team was aware and presumably working to improve the hotline responsiveness). The blank screen issue itself likely required e123 (the portal provider) to investigate ‚Äì possibly a browser compatibility issue or account sync problem. The interim solution was Ron calling the broker back and ensuring they wouldn‚Äôt be left without help[[3]](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:5bc83d83a48a42ee8b3177c9bb4b7f2f@thread.v2/1760033312713?context=%7B%22contextType%22:%22chat%22%7D). In all cases, the **response time** was very fast ‚Äì brokers received replies and help on the same day, often within hours or minutes, reflecting the team‚Äôs high priority on access issues.

**People involved:** The **Broker Relations and Support team** is front and center here. Sheri Hernandez, as the Sales Director for Broker Relations, took point on most of these emails, either replying to the broker or forwarding instructions to her team. She frequently CC‚Äôd or directed tasks to Mark Cetola (the Sales Enablement Analyst) and Steven Mezidor, indicating these team members serve as hands-on support for technical troubleshooting[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). Ron Zighelboim (Strategic Partnerships) also got directly involved, especially if a broker reached out to him or if Tony delegated an issue to him[[3]](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:5bc83d83a48a42ee8b3177c9bb4b7f2f@thread.v2/1760033312713?context=%7B%22contextType%22:%22chat%22%7D)[[3]](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/message/19:5bc83d83a48a42ee8b3177c9bb4b7f2f@thread.v2/1760033312713?context=%7B%22contextType%22:%22chat%22%7D). Anthony Horner (VP of Rev Ops) was in the loop on all major issues; he provided leadership escalation when needed (like coordinating with IT or reinforcing process changes)[[4]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaBAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). We also see that an official group email **[BrokerSupport@innovage.com](mailto:BrokerSupport@innovage.com)** exists[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem) ‚Äì brokers often emailed this address which would reach Sheri‚Äôs team. Sheri‚Äôs rapid replies to those, sometimes within hours early in the morning, show that the **Broker Support unit is actively monitored** and responsive.

Overall, **portal-related issues were resolved through a combination of personal assistance (ensuring each broker can log in successfully) and system fixes (addressing any root causes like URL issues)**. The recurring nature of password/login problems has likely led the team to emphasize training (discussed later) and maintain a high-touch support approach for brokers struggling with access.

### 2. Enrollment Application & Data Glitches

**Nature of issues:** Some broker communications highlighted **problems with the flow of data** from the brokers‚Äô enrollment platform (Enrollment123, referred to as e123) into InnovAge‚Äôs internal systems (CRM). Two specific issues emerged:

- **Missing email field blocking application transfer:** It was identified that if a prospect‚Äôs email address was blank on an application submitted by a broker, that application did not get ingested into the CRM[[5]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaGAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). This is a serious issue because many elderly applicants **do not have email** (as Sheri noted, ‚ÄúMany older adults don‚Äôt use email or have a computer‚Äù)[[5]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaGAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). In such cases, brokers would leave that field empty, and those applications would effectively vanish from the pipeline due to a system rule expecting an email. The broker might not even realize their app didn‚Äôt go through.
- **Applications stuck with no status update:** Sheri Hernandez pulled a report on eight applications and found that none had any status in the system (not even marked as received)[[6]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzZ7AAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). These were presumably applications submitted via the broker portal that should have shown at least a ‚Äúreceived/pending‚Äù status in InnovAge‚Äôs CRM or tracking spreadsheet. The absence of status meant the applications could have been lost or not processed downstream, which could delay enrollment or commission payments.

**How they were addressed:** Both issues were treated with urgency, given they affect enrollments (the lifeblood of sales):

- Sheri immediately **escalated the problems to the operations and IT team**. For the missing email issue, Anthony Horner was directly involved ‚Äì he initially raised the concern that e123 apps weren‚Äôt transferring when email was missing, prompting Sheri‚Äôs input about the real-world prevalence of missing emails[[5]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaGAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). For the blank status issue, Sheri explicitly asked Tony and his team to investigate and escalate[[6]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzZ7AAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem).

### 3. Lead Submission & Commission Tracking Issues

**Nature of issues:** This category includes cases where an **administrative or process gap** led to potential issues in tracking broker contributions ‚Äì specifically:

- A broker‚Äôs **lead not being captured** in the broker system because they did not follow the standard process.
- Questions or confusion regarding **commission payments**, including how much brokers and FMOs are paid for each enrollment.

These issues are about ensuring brokers are properly credited and compensated for their work, which is crucial for broker satisfaction and compliance.

**Lead submission bypass (InnSight vs e123):** The notable incident was when a broker from FMO _Health Plan Markets_ (broker Lamont Richardson) generated a new patient lead (prospect Gracie Benford) via a phone call to InnovAge‚Äôs contact center, instead of entering it through the e123 broker portal[[8]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR8dAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). The contact center logged the lead in InnovAge‚Äôs internal system (often called ‚ÄúInnSight‚Äù in context, perhaps an internal CRM interface), but because the broker didn‚Äôt input it in e123, the broker‚Äôs account had no record of it. This not only risks the lead being processed outside the usual workflow but also means the broker might not automatically get commission credit because the lead isn‚Äôt tied to them in the e123 system. Anthony Horner explicitly flagged that to **‚Äúensure commissions flow as expected,‚Äù** they needed to get that lead into e123 retroactively[[8]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR8dAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem).

**Commission payout inquiries:** Separately, there was a need to clarify the **exact commission amounts** for broker sales. InnovAge adheres to CMS (Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services) guidelines for broker compensation by state/region. The communications showed that someone (likely the Enrollment123 team or an FMO partner) asked for a table of ‚Äúhow much we should be paying‚Äù for initial and renewal enrollments in different regions[[9]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR75AAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). This is fundamental for both configuring systems (so that payments are calculated correctly) and for answering any FMO‚Äôs questions about their earning potential. The broker contracts contained these numbers, but a clear summary was needed for quick reference.

**How they were addressed:**

- **Process enforcement for lead entries:** Upon discovering the missed lead entry, the response was twofold: fix the immediate data gap and change the process to prevent repeats. Ron Zighelboim reached out to Angela Vabulas (Enrollment123‚Äôs VP of Professional Services) for advice[[8]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR8dAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem), since this scenario crosses systems. She also raised a technical point: if a lead is added later in e123 after already existing in CRM, they need to avoid duplicates by linking data (e.g., creating a matching member ID)[[8]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR8dAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). ## Patterns and Insights

Across all these categories, several **patterns emerge** in how InnovAge handles FMO broker requests:

- **High Touch, High Priority Support:** Broker inquiries, especially around portal access and sales opportunities (leads, apps), are treated with urgency. The communications show same-day responses and often resolution or action within hours. This rapid turnaround is crucial during peak periods (e.g., around October, likely Medicare open enrollment season). Brokers are often working on tight timelines with clients, so InnovAge‚Äôs ability to solve issues quickly builds trust.
    
- **Cross-Functional Collaboration:** The resolution of issues frequently involves _multiple teams_: Sales (Broker Relations), IT, and the external platform partner (Enrollment123). Instead of siloing a problem, the team loops in whoever is needed. For example, a single email chain about a lead involved broker support, contact center, IT, and vendor representatives all together[[8]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR8dAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem)[[8]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR8dAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). This collaborative approach means brokers get comprehensive solutions (not ‚Äúthat‚Äôs not my department‚Äù responses). It also spreads knowledge ‚Äì e.g., Mark Cetola and others are copied on many threads for learning purposes, so the next time a similar issue arises, more people are equipped to handle it.
    
- **Documentation and Process Improvement:** There is an emphasis on **capturing issues in FAQs and templates** to educate the team and brokers. Tony‚Äôs request to add the edge-case lead scenario to the FAQ[[8]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR8dAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem) is one example; Ron creating standardized email templates for brokers (mentioned in older Teams messages) is another. Each solved issue becomes a learning opportunity to refine training materials or system logic. Over time, this reduces the frequency of certain questions. For instance, if many brokers ask about commissions, they might publish a one-pager with those details proactively.
    
- **Recurring Issues:** Some issues tend to recur (password resets, account help, basic ‚Äúhow-to‚Äù questions), whereas others are one-off or seasonal (commission tables updated annually, unusual lead scenarios). The recurring ones are handled almost routinely now ‚Äì Sheri‚Äôs team likely expects that every morning they might have a few brokers needing password help, and they handle those almost automatically. The rarer issues get escalated and solved, and then often turned into standard practice (so they won‚Äôt be as rare in terms of being known, even if occurrence is low). The **most frequent category by volume** is clearly _portal access issues_, followed by general ‚Äúhow do I‚Ä¶?‚Äù usage questions. More complex technical problems (like integration bugs) were fewer but impactful, each triggering a deeper fix.
    
- **Communication Tone and Professionalism:** Throughout the emails, the tone remains professional, courteous, and solution-focused. Sheri often thanks people for alerting her (‚ÄúGreat, thank you for letting us know!‚Äù to Brandie after the portal started working[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem)). She signs off with _‚ÄúRespectfully‚Äù_ in more formal responses[[9]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR75AAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem). This tone likely extends to broker communications ‚Äì even when a broker is frustrated (e.g., ‚Äúlink not working, please advise‚Äù[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem)), the response is patient and helpful (‚ÄúHi, that‚Äôs weird, I checked‚Ä¶we‚Äôll help you troubleshoot‚Äù[[1]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzaHAAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem)). Maintaining this positive tone helps de-escalate issues and keeps the partnership vibe intact.
    
- **Use of Data and Attachments:** The team uses data to drive solutions ‚Äì attaching reports of problematic applications[[6]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAAGkzZ7AAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem), referencing contract documents for commissions[[9]](https://outlook.office365.com/owa/?ItemID=AAMkAGRhMjFjYTg0LWJlYzUtNGQwNi04MzNkLTM0ZjBjZjc4Y2VjOABGAAAAAAC2ppWvS%2bqsTIOptiT2tdoNBwB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADY6mnAAB387hUljSAT7LDAYnxTJx3AAADZR75AAA%3d\&exvsurl=1\&viewmodel=ReadMessageItem), and linking training materials. This thoroughness means that when they escalate to, say, the vendor, they provide evidence (which speeds up vendor support). It also means that any advice given to brokers is backed by the official info (e.g. commission numbers from the contract, not an off-the-cuff guess).
    
- **Frequency and Context:** The concentration of multiple issues around the same timeframe (early/mid October 2025) suggests that this period might have been a go-live or ramp-up phase for the FMO broker program.
